Here are three things you must do when visiting the Vancouver Lookout.

Number one: The glass elevator. The viewing deck is only accessible via elevator. This glass elevator takes you up 168 meters (553 feet) to enjoy a 360° view of the city. If you are scared of heights you can always hold on to the railing until you arrive at the top 🛗⬆️

Number 2: The Self-Guided Audio Tour. Learn about Vancouver through this complimentary self-guided audio tour available in six languages. Just scan our QR Code from your device, choose a language and you are good to go. We also have free Wi-Fi and informational plaques that are distributed around the viewing deck so you can learn even more about our city’s history and culture 🎧📖

Number three: Taking pictures. A picture provides a unique perception of an experience, a way to keep long-lasting memories to yourself and to share with loved ones. Feel free to ask our team members to take photos throughout your visit, they will always put in their best effort to find the right angle and balance the background lighting 📸🤳

There are also many chairs and tables distributed around the viewing deck, so you and your family can sit down, relax from a long day or plan your next stop while watching an amazing view 🪑🗺️

Tickets are available online or upon arrival at our cashless self-serve station - link in the bio.

Have you visited must visit attraction in Vancouver, BC? @vancouverlookout is a must visit for locals and tourists.

The journey begins with a 40-second glass elevator ride, taking you 168 meters (553 feet) up to our panoramic viewing platform. Once there, you can savor breathtaking 360° vistas of Vancouver’s picturesque scenery. The Vancouver Lookout can be found atop the renowned Harbour Centre, one of Vancouver’s iconic landmarks. You can discover more about Vancouver through informative panels scattered around the deck or by embarking on a complimentary self-guided audio tour.

📍 Vancouver Lookout
555 W Hastings St, Vancouver, BC V6B 4N6

O dia que eu vi Vancouver do alto!! 🌇

Eu sempre gosto de ver os lugares por outras perspectivas e aproveitei o Vancouver Lookout para ver a cidade de cima!! 🤩

Confesso que minha expectativa quanto ao mirante estava mais alta, achei que a vista era mais aberta (que fosse de vidro do chão ao teto). Na verdade, ele só é aberto de vidro na parte de cima 🤷🏼‍♀️

De qualquer forma, a cidade vista de cima é muito bonita e essas cores outonais a deixaram ainda mais charmosa 🍁

Para visitar o mirante, o ticket pode ser comprado antecipado ou na porta e custou CAD18 (+/- R$65). Você pode ficar quanto tempo quiser e na visita está incluso o audioguia (também em português) que explica um pouco sobre os principais pontos da cidade.

Uma alternativa é subir mais para o final da tarde para ver a cidade tanto de dia quanto de noite!!

E aí, o que achou que valeu a pena subir para ver Vancouver de cima?! Deixa um 💙 se gostou das imagens!

Happy New Year from the Vancouver Lookout team to all of our guests who made this 2023 so special!✨️🌠

We welcomed amazing people from all over the world and we thank you for letting us be part of your memories while visiting #Vancouver 🏞🌁🏙

And a special thank you to all of our tourism partners including attractions, hotels, travel agencies and many more! 🥂 Here is to a great 2024🎉🎊

One thing you must do when visiting Vancouver is making a stop to the Vancouver Lookout: 

You start by taking a  glass elevator up 168 meters where you can enjoy a 360° view that includes Stanley Park, historic Gastown, the Northshore mountains. The Vancouver Lookout has been an iconic element of the city’s skyline since 1977.

We had so much fun taking in the views from the top of Vancouver, we were able to spot a lot of the places that we visited and got amazing views of the harbor and the surrounding mountains. 

If you happen to catch the perfect timing, you can see as the sun starts going down and all of the lights of beautiful downtown Vancouver start to light up the city. 

Vancouver Lookout should be on everyone’s list when visiting Vancouver! Thank you @VancouverLookout for #hosting us and showing us a different perspective of beautiful Vancouver.
